Script for installation of Redis 2.6.4 as a service on Amazon Elastic Beanstalk instances. It may probably fit other purposes as well. Just check out 'redis-install-script.sh' file ;)
This is a modification of the original Saxenap's script, optimized for automatic deployment scripts.
Note: Please make sure you have superuser privileges

Usage:
----
1. wget https://raw.github.com/saxenap/install-redis-amazon-linux-centos/master/redis-install-script.sh
2. chmod 777 redis-install-script.sh
3. ./redis-install-script.sh

References:
